-- Thailand’s IRPC Said to Seek Low-Sulfur Oil Cargo for Early May
-- B y   R a m s e y   A l - R i k a b i
-- 2013-03-13T04:55:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-13/thailand-s-irpc-said-to-seek-low-sulfur-oil-cargo-for-early-may.html
IRPC Pcl (IRPC) , an oil refiner and
petrochemical maker based in Thailand, is seeking to buy 600,000
to 1 million barrels of low-sulfur, or sweet, crude for delivery
from May 1 to May 5, according to two people who participate in
the market.  The shipment is to be sold on a delivered basis to the
company’s 215,000 barrel-a-day plant in Rayong province, the
people said, asking not to be identified because they aren’t
authorized to speak to the media. The tender closes at noon
today in Bangkok and offers are valid until 6 p.m. tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ramsey Al-Rikabi in Singapore at 
